11. Circumstances Triggering Obligation to Remedy.

In this Agreement, the following circumstances shall be deemed as triggering the obligee's responsibility to rectify the situation within a reasonable timeframe:

a) The obligor's persistent failure to perform any of its obligations under this Agreement;
b) Any action or inaction by the obligor that materially breaches this Agreement or contravenes any applicable law or regulation;
c) The filing, institution, continuation, or non-dismissal of any legal proceedings against either party relating to the subject matter of this Agreement, unless such proceedings have been brought in good faith and with proper cause;
d) Any other event or circumstance that, if left unaddressed, could reasonably be expected to materially impair the performance of the obligor's obligations under this Agreement.

In the event any of the above circumstances arise, the obligee shall have the right, but not the obligation, to take such reasonable actions as it deems necessary to protect its interests, provided that it shall use its best efforts to minimize any potential adverse impact on the obligor's business operations and financial condition.
